VARIOUS ENVIRONMETS USED FOR PYHTON PROGRAMMING:
The most common environment for Python Programming can be bifurcated into these which include:
•	Python default interpreter and IDE (Integrated Development Environment )called as IDLE
•	Third party Code Editors and IDE
•	Cloud Based IDE’s like GitLab Web IDE , Code Anywhere
•	Some other examples of code editors and IDEs that can be used for Python development include Sublime Text, Visual Studio Code, Atom etc.
•	Some popular open source Python IDE’s include Eclipse, Pycharm, Eric, Spyder etc.
